text.section:
The Commission may grant a waiver under this section only if the applicant:
pays the application fee required under § 17-307 of this subtitle for the license for which the applicant is applying;
provides adequate evidence that the applicant meets the qualifications otherwise required by this subtitle for the license for which the applicant is applying;
submits a certified copy of the applicant's license from the other state that is comparable or equivalent to the license for which the applicant is applying; and
if the applicant holds a license comparable or equivalent to a real estate broker license, provides adequate evidence that the applicant actively maintains an office in the other state.
